  "response": "The amount of human excreta produced by a single person can vary based on factors such as diet, fluid intake, metabolism, and overall health. However, on average:\n\n1. **Urine**: A typical adult urinates approximately 800 to 2,000 milliliters per day, depending largely on fluid intake.\n\n2. **Feces**: An average adult produces about 100 to 250 grams of feces per day.\n\nThese numbers can vary widely among individuals and populations, but they give a general idea of the average production of human excreta per person daily.",
